WEBVTT

00:00.034 --> 00:01.624
<i>Previously on "The Bold Type"...</i>

00:01.642 --> 00:02.980
Maybe the two of us should hit the town

00:03.043 --> 00:04.830
- one of these days?
- Yeah.

00:05.984 --> 00:10.202
Brook just put $500 worth of
cocaine on my Scarlet card.

00:10.237 --> 00:12.749
- What? How?
- Oh, my God. I don't know.

00:12.784 --> 00:14.484
<i>This is where you belong, Jane.</i>

00:14.519 --> 00:15.552
- I know.
- So what are you going to do?

00:15.587 --> 00:16.720
<i>Go see Jacqueline</i>

00:16.755 --> 00:18.488
<i>and see if I can come back.</i>

00:18.523 --> 00:21.625
I'm not sure that that is
the best thing for you.

00:21.660 --> 00:24.427
<i>You need to live in this failure.</i>

00:24.463 --> 00:25.629
You must be Kat.

00:25.664 --> 00:27.797
- I'm Leila.
- Right, Leila.

00:27.833 --> 00:29.733
Adena promised I could
borrow her tripod.

00:29.768 --> 00:31.735
Can I stop by the next
couple days and grab it?

00:31.770 --> 00:33.637
<i>Oh, Adena's not here.</i>

00:39.919 --> 00:42.479
- Good morning, sunshine.
- Ow!

00:42.514 --> 00:44.681
- [laughs] Come on.
- Light burns my skin.

00:44.716 --> 00:47.450
Kat is here and she is
making you a greasy brunch.

00:47.486 --> 00:49.786
- Hey.
- Oh, my God.

00:49.821 --> 00:51.821
Hangovers are, like,
90% about your attitude.

00:51.857 --> 00:53.657
Come on!

00:53.692 --> 00:55.525
[tongue clicks]

00:55.560 --> 00:58.662
Couldn't sleep last night
so I stayed up, taught myself how

00:58.697 --> 01:01.531
- to make the perfect frittata.
- Oh.

01:01.566 --> 01:03.466
It's all in how you whip the eggs.

01:03.502 --> 01:05.769
- Afraid to go to sleep?
- Sex dreams come at night.

01:05.804 --> 01:07.637
It was one dream,

01:07.673 --> 01:09.472
and it only happened
because Adena's away

01:09.508 --> 01:10.674
and I miss her, so...

01:10.709 --> 01:12.776
You know, when she gets back it'll stop.

01:12.811 --> 01:14.411
How was your night?

01:14.446 --> 01:16.346
I was out until 3:00 in the morning

01:16.381 --> 01:18.748
with Brook and the entire
Argentinean polo team.

01:18.784 --> 01:22.719
Yeah, I'm aware. You kept yelling
at the microwave to do its job better.

01:22.754 --> 01:24.621
Vamos, el microwave. Vamos.

01:24.656 --> 01:26.489
Shouldn't take that long
to heat up frozen pizza.

01:26.525 --> 01:28.591
So this is a lot of partying for you.

01:28.627 --> 01:31.695
Is it because, maybe,
you saw Richard with that woman?

01:31.730 --> 01:33.596
Oh, God, no.

01:33.632 --> 01:36.599
I mean... I'm making so many contacts

01:36.635 --> 01:38.768
and, you know, networking.

01:38.804 --> 01:40.370
I feel really focused on my career

01:40.405 --> 01:41.504
- right now, you know?
- Yeah.

01:41.540 --> 01:42.772
[cell phone dings]

01:42.808 --> 01:44.574
- Oh, my God.
- What?

01:44.609 --> 01:46.443
I got nominated for a Mandy Award.

01:46.478 --> 01:47.544
[gasping]

01:47.579 --> 01:48.778
- That's amazing.
- Yes.

01:48.814 --> 01:50.513
- What is that?
- Yeah, what is it?

01:50.549 --> 01:52.816
Oh, it's a women's
lifestyle magazine award.

01:52.851 --> 01:55.385
- What? That's amazing!
- Oh, my God.

01:55.420 --> 01:57.387
- We need some champagne.
- [imitates heaving]

01:57.422 --> 02:00.757
The category is outstanding achievement
in biographical feature writing

02:00.792 --> 02:03.493
for my "Carry The Weight" article.

02:03.528 --> 02:05.495
That's the one you
wrote about Jacqueline?

02:05.530 --> 02:07.364
- Mm-hmm.
- Three, two...

02:07.399 --> 02:09.332
Oh, my God. So loud.

02:09.368 --> 02:12.602
Oh, come on.
Here, have some hair of the dog.

02:12.637 --> 02:15.372
- That's a lot.
- Yeah. She needs it.

02:15.407 --> 02:17.307
What?

02:18.400 --> 02:19.442
What's happening?

02:19.478 --> 02:20.543
- [whimpering]
- Are you okay?

02:20.579 --> 02:22.379
Just go slowly.

02:22.414 --> 02:23.613
No... no, don't do it.

02:23.648 --> 02:25.382
[heaves]

02:29.961 --> 02:32.389
- Photo shoot with Jacqueline. [groans]
- _

02:32.424 --> 02:34.524
Hey.

02:34.559 --> 02:37.627
- Hi.
- What are you doing out here?

02:37.662 --> 02:39.362
You know, just stooping it.

02:39.398 --> 02:40.697
Are those for me?

02:40.732 --> 02:43.433
Well, it depends.
Are you an award nominee?

02:43.468 --> 02:44.667
I am.

02:44.703 --> 02:46.469
Well, good. Works out then.

02:46.505 --> 02:47.804
[chuckles]

02:47.839 --> 02:49.706
Thank you.

02:51.710 --> 02:53.810
So getting nominated
for an award for writing,

02:53.845 --> 02:55.812
that's pretty impressive.

02:55.847 --> 02:58.448
Yeah, it is.

02:58.483 --> 03:00.417
Your voice is kind of high right now.

03:00.452 --> 03:02.285
What? No.

03:02.320 --> 03:03.686
[scoffs] Jane, come on.

03:03.722 --> 03:06.523
[groans] Fine.

03:06.558 --> 03:08.658
It's a nomination for
an article that I wrote

03:08.693 --> 03:10.360
when I was at Scarlet.

03:10.395 --> 03:12.295
Before Jacqueline rejected me.

03:12.330 --> 03:14.731
Yeah, but now you've got
a Mandy nomination.

03:14.766 --> 03:17.300
You've never been rejected before,
have you?

03:18.503 --> 03:21.304
No, it's the accent.

03:21.339 --> 03:23.540
[sighs] I mean...

03:23.575 --> 03:27.510
when I went back and asked for my job
and Jacqueline said no...

03:27.546 --> 03:30.747
all I could think was,
"Did I ruin my career?"

03:30.782 --> 03:32.649
But then I sold a few pieces.

03:32.684 --> 03:34.651
The article I wrote about you came out.

03:34.686 --> 03:37.387
I feel like I'm finally moving on.

03:37.422 --> 03:39.422
Exactly, so what's the problem?

03:39.458 --> 03:41.357
This nomination and...

03:41.393 --> 03:44.494
With Jacqueline,
it just pulls me back in.

03:44.529 --> 03:46.329
[sighs]

03:46.364 --> 03:48.398
I think you're thinking
about this all wrong.

03:48.433 --> 03:50.333
I mean, I'm sure there's a
lot of magazines out there

03:50.368 --> 03:53.336
that would love a piece
written by a Mandy winner.

03:53.371 --> 03:54.604
So stop looking backwards

03:54.639 --> 03:56.739
and capitalize on the
buzz of the nomination.

04:01.713 --> 04:04.681
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

04:04.716 --> 04:09.586
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:09.621 --> 04:12.322
I saw Angie's Snap story comparing

04:12.357 --> 04:14.557
single-payer healthcare
to "The Bachelor."

04:14.593 --> 04:17.360
Seems like your team's
already doing a fantastic job.

04:17.394 --> 04:19.696
Yeah, thanks. I think so too.

04:19.731 --> 04:23.500
We're working on a social media campaign
for Scarlet's Mandy nom right now.

04:23.535 --> 04:25.301
Congratulations, by the way.

04:25.337 --> 04:26.703
Jane's the one who
deserves all the credit.

04:26.738 --> 04:29.539
- How is she, by the way?
- She's good.

04:29.574 --> 04:31.374
She's stoked.

04:31.409 --> 04:33.343
Good. Glad to hear that.

04:33.378 --> 04:34.744
- [cell phone dings]
- Yeah...

04:34.745 --> 04:37.645
_

04:37.716 --> 04:39.782
Kat, coming?

04:39.818 --> 04:42.719
Yes, yeah. Sorry.

04:48.827 --> 04:50.593
You're 20 minutes late, Red.

04:50.629 --> 04:52.562
Yes, but only because
I was getting you a gift.

04:52.597 --> 04:55.598
This better be Ativan.
Or Sour Patch Kids.

04:56.835 --> 05:00.303
I'm a complex man
with varied addictions.

05:02.607 --> 05:05.742
Vintage Van Cleef. Gorgeous.

05:05.777 --> 05:07.443
How did you procure these?

05:07.479 --> 05:09.512
Brooke Langely. Man, that girl

05:09.548 --> 05:11.347
has a lot of connections.

05:11.383 --> 05:13.316
I'm sure she does.

05:13.351 --> 05:15.451
You taking care of yourself?

05:15.487 --> 05:17.720
You look a little puffy.

05:19.491 --> 05:21.591
I have a keen eye.

05:21.626 --> 05:23.359
It's my job to notice these things.

05:23.395 --> 05:24.694
I am.

05:24.729 --> 05:27.297
And more importantly
I'm taking care of you.

05:27.332 --> 05:28.731
I'll be right back with coffee.

05:33.672 --> 05:35.705
She's not available.

05:35.740 --> 05:39.342
Okay, well, can you let her
know that Jane Sloan called?

05:39.377 --> 05:40.610
Yes.

05:40.645 --> 05:42.745
Yes, it's my first nomination.
Thank you.

05:44.482 --> 05:45.715
Oh, she is available now?

05:45.750 --> 05:47.550
Great.

05:47.586 --> 05:49.652
I would love to sit down with you.

05:49.688 --> 05:52.689
Lunch at Babbo? Yes, yes.

05:52.724 --> 05:55.391
It's "S-L-O-A-N."

05:55.427 --> 05:57.460
And please tell Mr. Seltzer
I have always wanted

05:57.495 --> 05:59.596
to write for "The Daily Review."

05:59.631 --> 06:01.297
He does?

06:01.333 --> 06:04.300
- <i>[upbeat music]</i>
- _

06:04.336 --> 06:05.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:05.704 --> 06:07.670
Yes!

06:10.375 --> 06:12.508
Need you to pull some
clothes from the closet.

06:12.544 --> 06:14.444
Medium to very sexy.

06:14.479 --> 06:16.546
Okay. It this for a photo shoot?

06:16.581 --> 06:18.514
A board member's date to the Mandy's.

06:18.550 --> 06:21.351
A request from Jacqueline to style her.

06:21.386 --> 06:22.719
Oh, wow.

06:22.754 --> 06:24.721
Size two, C Cup?

06:24.756 --> 06:26.456
One of the board members
trading in his wife

06:26.491 --> 06:28.291
for a newer model?

06:28.326 --> 06:30.760
No, this one isn't married.
At least not yet.

06:30.795 --> 06:32.662
Richard Hunter.

06:32.697 --> 06:34.631
You know who he is, right?
I think he put in a good word

06:34.666 --> 06:36.399
when I hired you.

06:36.434 --> 06:39.402
<i>[somber music]</i>

06:39.437 --> 06:41.337
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:41.706 --> 06:43.506
"The Daily Review" is interested

06:43.541 --> 06:46.509
in fresh perspectives,
and as much as I may wish

06:46.544 --> 06:48.478
Millennials were relegated
to the punchlines

06:48.513 --> 06:50.188
it seems your voices are the only ones

06:50.282 --> 06:52.448
people are interested
in hearing these days.

06:52.484 --> 06:54.417
Thank you?

06:54.452 --> 06:57.420
It would be a huge honor
to write for your magazine.

06:57.455 --> 06:59.355
I have a story that
would be perfect for you.

06:59.391 --> 07:00.690
Uh, what's that?

07:00.725 --> 07:02.558
A follow-up to your
"Carry The Weight" piece

07:02.594 --> 07:04.627
about Jacqueline Carlyle.

07:06.431 --> 07:08.364
I'm eager to write about something new.

07:08.400 --> 07:09.699
Something new?

07:09.734 --> 07:12.669
You wrote about the MeToo
movement before there was one.

07:12.704 --> 07:14.671
There's so much more to explore.

07:14.706 --> 07:16.472
- Well, what about...
- The domino effect,

07:16.508 --> 07:18.508
how the brave acts
of powerful women like

07:18.543 --> 07:21.311
Jacqueline Carlyle
inspired other victims

07:21.346 --> 07:22.578
to speak their truth.

07:22.614 --> 07:24.747
One woman steps forward,
then another and another

07:24.783 --> 07:27.550
until you have a movement, so...

07:28.653 --> 07:31.754
A feature in "The Daily Review."
What do you think?

07:33.625 --> 07:35.758
That sounds great.

07:37.429 --> 07:39.595
I know what you should dress her in.

07:39.631 --> 07:41.497
Uncomfortable shoes, itchy taffeta,

07:41.533 --> 07:43.599
something super hippy.

07:43.635 --> 07:45.468
I'm not pulling ugly clothes for her.

07:45.503 --> 07:46.669
Ugh, you're a saint.

07:46.705 --> 07:49.851
It isn't in my DNA to put somebody
in something that's not beautiful,

07:49.875 --> 07:53.576
even if that someone is Richard's...

07:53.611 --> 07:55.511
new girlfriend.

07:57.382 --> 07:58.715
Hey, how do we feel about this?

07:58.750 --> 08:00.683
Oh. It's cute.

08:00.719 --> 08:02.685
Leila invited me out
with her friends tonight.

08:02.721 --> 08:04.554
Leila sex dream Leila?

08:04.589 --> 08:05.655
Okay, that's not why I'm going.

08:05.690 --> 08:08.257
Okay. Why you going?

08:08.293 --> 08:09.659
I don't know, 'cause Adena introduced me

08:09.694 --> 08:11.728
to this whole scene that
I never even knew existed,

08:11.763 --> 08:13.496
and I guess I'm just curious.

08:13.531 --> 08:15.598
Okay. Go have fun.

08:15.633 --> 08:18.434
- You should wear that shirt.
- Okay.

08:21.673 --> 08:24.640
<i>[Sizzy Rocket's "Girls to the Front"]</i>

08:25.450 --> 08:27.710
<i>♪ I'm from another planet,
this nation... ♪</i>

08:27.746 --> 08:29.746
Oh. Thank you.

08:36.388 --> 08:38.287
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

08:38.323 --> 08:40.423
Oh. That's okay.

08:41.525 --> 08:43.458
Congratulations on the nomination.

08:43.495 --> 08:45.695
It's a big deal for you,
a big deal for Scarlet.

08:45.730 --> 08:47.463
Thank you, and congrats to you too.

08:47.499 --> 08:49.465
- Thank you.
- Okay.

08:49.501 --> 08:51.734
Let's have you both
seated next to each other.

08:51.770 --> 08:54.337
Oh, okay. Seated.

08:58.543 --> 09:01.444
So tell me what you've
been up to lately.

09:01.479 --> 09:04.447
Uh, well,
I just had lunch with Jeff Seltzer

09:04.482 --> 09:06.549
- from "The Daily Review."
- Oh.

09:06.584 --> 09:10.520
He wants me to write a follow-up
to the "Carry The Weight" article.

09:10.555 --> 09:12.622
Really? What's the angle?

09:13.725 --> 09:16.359
Let's have you stand up.

09:16.394 --> 09:18.594
Well, it's about the domino effect.

09:18.630 --> 09:21.564
How when one person
in a position of power

09:21.599 --> 09:24.734
steps forward it inspires
others to do the same.

09:24.769 --> 09:29.672
Well, it was incredibly healing for me
to tell my story, and...

09:29.707 --> 09:32.475
it really means a lot
that my coming forward

09:32.510 --> 09:34.410
has had a positive impact.

09:34.446 --> 09:36.479
And I owe that to you.

09:37.782 --> 09:39.482
Perfect. Thanks, ladies.

09:39.517 --> 09:40.650
We're good.

09:40.685 --> 09:42.485
All right, well,

09:42.520 --> 09:46.422
it seems like the freelance lifestyle's
working out for you.

09:46.458 --> 09:48.324
It is.

09:48.359 --> 09:49.625
I actually just wrote an article

09:49.661 --> 09:52.528
about women's healthcare
for "Next Century Magazine."

09:52.564 --> 09:55.398
I'm happy to see you happy, Jane.

09:55.433 --> 09:56.632
Thank you.

09:56.668 --> 09:58.501
And now I've got to run.

09:58.536 --> 10:01.370
Oh, right,
Wednesday afternoon pitch meeting.

10:01.406 --> 10:02.538
See you at the awards.

10:02.574 --> 10:04.307
Yes, you will.

10:14.419 --> 10:17.520
<i>[Kaytranada's "Together"]</i>

10:17.555 --> 10:21.491
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:21.526 --> 10:23.392
<i>♪ It's hard to let it go ♪</i>

10:23.428 --> 10:25.695
<i>♪ Let it flow away and never mind it ♪</i>

10:25.730 --> 10:27.597
<i>♪ It seems so much more ♪</i>

10:27.632 --> 10:29.565
<i>♪ So intense, so you never find a way ♪</i>

10:29.601 --> 10:33.769
<i>♪ To forgive, to forget,
to be unconditional ♪</i>

10:33.805 --> 10:37.707
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:37.742 --> 10:41.611
<i>♪ We don't have to fight no more ♪</i>

10:41.646 --> 10:45.715
<i>♪ This isn't the time to
be tumbling on the floor ♪</i>

10:45.750 --> 10:49.752
<i>♪ We just have to walk
through that door... ♪</i>

10:49.787 --> 10:52.655
Kat.

10:52.690 --> 10:55.658
- Hi. Hey.
- Oh, hey.

10:55.693 --> 10:56.826
I'm so happy you came.

10:56.861 --> 10:58.528
I'm sorry I flaked the other night.

10:58.563 --> 10:59.863
It's all good.

10:59.925 --> 11:02.598
Guys, this is Kat, Adena's girlfriend.

11:02.634 --> 11:03.766
Hello.

11:03.801 --> 11:05.535
Head of Social Media at Scarlet

11:05.570 --> 11:07.670
- and all around badass.
- Oh, thank you.

11:07.705 --> 11:09.438
Here.

11:09.474 --> 11:11.307
Drink up, woman.

11:11.342 --> 11:12.642
You've got a lot of catching up to do.

11:12.677 --> 11:15.311
- Shots, okay.
- Cheers.

11:21.719 --> 11:24.737
I was so worried about making
this story not about Jacqueline

11:24.743 --> 11:28.344
but I don't think it's
gonna be a problem.

11:28.379 --> 11:29.745
Oh, yeah? Tell me.

11:29.781 --> 11:31.647
Well, there are so many women

11:31.683 --> 11:33.516
who have spoken out
and are inspiring others

11:33.551 --> 11:34.684
to do the same.

11:34.719 --> 11:36.485
It really is like a domino effect.

11:36.521 --> 11:38.554
I already have so many
people who I've interviewed

11:38.590 --> 11:42.825
and I think it's gonna be
a really positive piece.

11:42.861 --> 11:44.594
That's great.

11:44.629 --> 11:47.396
And I think Jacqueline
was actually impressed.

11:47.432 --> 11:48.631
How did the photo shoot go?

11:48.666 --> 11:50.666
Well, at first I was really nervous,

11:50.702 --> 11:52.768
but then after seeing Jacqueline

11:52.804 --> 11:56.372
I just remembered how much I like her.

11:56.407 --> 11:59.475
The whole thing
was really nice, actually.

11:59.510 --> 12:05.348
I don't know. I was so angry at her
for not bringing me back, but...

12:05.383 --> 12:07.750
the truth is... is she was right.

12:07.785 --> 12:09.685
This time has been good for me.

12:09.721 --> 12:12.488
Sounds like you really turned a corner.

12:12.523 --> 12:14.490
Yeah, I have.

12:14.525 --> 12:18.427
I just want this piece to
really honor Jacqueline.

12:18.463 --> 12:20.663
She deserves that.

12:20.698 --> 12:22.765
I'm so glad you're
feeling better about this.

12:22.800 --> 12:24.734
I am.

12:27.372 --> 12:28.704
So, um...

12:28.740 --> 12:32.608
Would you wanna go
with me to the awards?

12:32.644 --> 12:34.610
I'd be honored.

12:34.646 --> 12:36.712
I'm assuming this would
be a three way date

12:36.748 --> 12:38.581
with Kat and Sutton, though right?

12:38.616 --> 12:40.383
We are a package deal.

12:40.418 --> 12:42.351
Uh-huh.

12:42.387 --> 12:43.686
And to think that just a few months ago

12:43.721 --> 12:45.588
I couldn't get a date
with a single woman.

12:45.623 --> 12:47.790
Well, you're welcome.

12:47.825 --> 12:49.558
[laptop dings]

12:53.398 --> 12:54.730
- _
- Oh.

12:54.766 --> 12:58.768
There is another woman who is interested
in being part of my story.

13:00.505 --> 13:02.438
[laptop dings]

13:02.473 --> 13:05.341
That's interesting.
She wants to meet me in person.

13:05.376 --> 13:07.376
Okay, cool.

13:07.412 --> 13:08.711
Can we stop working now?

13:08.746 --> 13:11.781
Yes, I just need to DM her really quick.

13:11.816 --> 13:15.318
Okay, but then I want to DM you.

13:15.353 --> 13:18.321
I don't think you know what that means.

13:18.356 --> 13:19.655
I don't.

13:19.691 --> 13:23.059
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

13:23.089 --> 13:24.760
This one's from the girl
at the end of the bar.

13:24.796 --> 13:26.729
Oh.

13:26.764 --> 13:28.531
Sweet, okay.

13:28.566 --> 13:30.466
This is like the third drink tonight,

13:30.501 --> 13:31.801
and from a different girl every time.

13:31.836 --> 13:34.370
Do people think I'm Solange
Knowles or something?

13:34.405 --> 13:35.738
- 'Cause you know, I get it...
- No.

13:35.773 --> 13:38.341
You're just kind of a
big deal around here.

13:38.376 --> 13:39.709
How? I've never been here before.

13:39.744 --> 13:42.645
Yeah, exactly.
The lesbian scene is so small.

13:42.680 --> 13:44.647
