Okay.

29:50.534 --> 29:52.534
Guess I'll see you at the table.

29:53.670 --> 29:56.471
Actually, um...

29:57.441 --> 30:00.408
there is something.

30:00.444 --> 30:02.410
I've still got it.

30:02.446 --> 30:04.546
What's up, Jane?

30:05.615 --> 30:08.550
Can we speak a little more privately?

30:08.585 --> 30:10.685
Um...

30:16.526 --> 30:19.427
So? What's up?

30:20.764 --> 30:23.732
Today I interviewed a woman, Elena,

30:23.767 --> 30:26.401
who worked at "News Today"
after you left.

30:26.436 --> 30:28.403
Oh.

30:29.740 --> 30:34.609
And she believes that she was assaulted
by the same man who assaulted you.

30:36.780 --> 30:39.414
It's devastating.

30:39.449 --> 30:43.685
To think another woman was victimized
by the same man who assaulted me.

30:45.822 --> 30:50.458
Your story inspired her to speak out.

30:50.494 --> 30:52.861
[sighs] But she said...

30:52.896 --> 30:55.563
she's upset with you
even though she knows

30:55.599 --> 30:57.599
you're not to blame.

30:57.634 --> 30:59.601
I didn't know this was her story

30:59.636 --> 31:01.803
when I agreed to meet with
her and I don't even know

31:01.838 --> 31:04.406
if I'm gonna use it, but...

31:04.441 --> 31:07.943
I needed you to know, just in case.

31:07.946 --> 31:10.615
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
we're about to get started.</i>

31:10.648 --> 31:13.581
<i>Would you kindly take your seats?</i>

31:13.617 --> 31:15.683
The ceremony's beginning.

31:24.024 --> 31:26.761
And now the Mandy's
honors this year's...

31:26.796 --> 31:27.929
- Oh.
- Okay!

31:27.949 --> 31:29.864
- We're almost there.
- These shoes are killing me.

31:29.899 --> 31:31.866
The nominees are

31:31.901 --> 31:34.836
Sondra Prokop,
"The Devil Went Down to Georgia,"

31:34.871 --> 31:38.606
an intriguing profile of the
embattled female coach...

31:39.343 --> 31:41.609
Thank you.

31:41.644 --> 31:44.979
Gloria Temez, for "Rising Tides,"

31:45.014 --> 31:47.048
a harrowing account of one woman's fight

31:47.051 --> 31:49.851
- against an ever-encroaching...
- [applause]

31:56.317 --> 31:59.794
Diane Myers,
"Do We Really Need Our Mother,"

31:59.829 --> 32:02.830
a heart-warming story of
a mother's journey home.

32:02.866 --> 32:04.932
[applause]

32:08.805 --> 32:11.873
And finally, Jane Sloan,
"Carry The Weight,"

32:11.908 --> 32:16.644
a poignant piece giving voice
to the survivors of sexual assault.

32:16.679 --> 32:18.913
[applause]

32:21.684 --> 32:24.819
And the winner is...

32:24.854 --> 32:27.655
Jane Sloan. Jane Sloan, Scarlet.

32:27.690 --> 32:28.990
I won?

32:29.025 --> 32:32.560
I think you need to give a speech now.

32:33.029 --> 32:34.796
[cheers and applause]

32:34.831 --> 32:37.799
<i>[warm music]</i>

32:37.834 --> 32:40.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:40.220 --> 32:42.670
Congratulations.

32:46.424 --> 32:50.978
Wow, um, this is so unexpected.

32:51.014 --> 32:52.980
But really, thank you.

32:53.016 --> 32:56.918
First, I would like to thank
all of the survivors

32:56.953 --> 33:00.788
out there for having
the courage to speak out.

33:00.824 --> 33:03.925
One voice can inspire others.

33:03.960 --> 33:06.527
One voice can start a movement.

33:06.563 --> 33:08.055
And in this case,

33:08.131 --> 33:11.732
that voice belongs
to Jacqueline Carlyle.

33:11.768 --> 33:14.702
[applause]

33:17.874 --> 33:23.444
Jacqueline was not only the subject
of this very difficult piece,

33:23.480 --> 33:26.381
she was also my editor,

33:26.416 --> 33:28.316
and my mentor.

33:28.351 --> 33:32.420
She pushed me to dig deeper
even when it was too painful.

33:33.523 --> 33:36.624
And she taught me that what matters most

33:36.660 --> 33:41.329
isn't your byline or these awards.

33:41.364 --> 33:43.698
What matters most is the story

33:43.733 --> 33:45.733
and the truth.

33:45.769 --> 33:48.703
In our personal lives
and the stories we tell,

33:48.738 --> 33:52.740
the truth must always come first.

33:52.776 --> 33:55.777
So... thank you.

33:55.812 --> 33:58.746
[applause]

33:58.782 --> 34:05.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:07.590 --> 34:09.623
[laughter]

34:11.561 --> 34:14.329
- Tiny spoon for tiny Jane.
- Thank you.

34:14.364 --> 34:15.563
Oh, boy.

34:15.598 --> 34:18.333
Jane Sloan, you just won a Mandy award.

34:18.368 --> 34:20.635
What are you gonna do next?

34:20.670 --> 34:23.404
- Disney World.
- Ooh, ooh.

34:23.440 --> 34:25.440
- I vote Epcot.
- Oh boy.

34:25.475 --> 34:27.308
[laughter]

34:27.344 --> 34:28.576
Hey, guys, I just want to say

34:28.610 --> 34:30.344
I know I've been kind
of a lot to deal with.

34:30.380 --> 34:31.746
No, don't apologize.

34:31.781 --> 34:33.481
I've just been partying
with Brooke so much lately

34:33.516 --> 34:36.516
and saying that it was because of all
the connections I was making,

34:36.553 --> 34:38.585
but really...

34:38.621 --> 34:41.589
man, losing Richard was just so hard.

34:41.623 --> 34:43.757
And then I just got so
wrapped up in my own thing,

34:43.793 --> 34:45.760
and I almost missed something
really important to you

34:45.795 --> 34:48.563
and that's lame as hell.

34:48.598 --> 34:50.531
- I love you.
- I love you.

34:50.567 --> 34:52.500
Does this mean I get my friend back?

34:52.534 --> 34:54.469
The one you drank?

34:54.504 --> 34:56.737
- Mm-hmm.
- Good.

34:56.773 --> 34:58.506
Okay, you have the spirit stick.

34:58.541 --> 34:59.707
Anything you want to say?

34:59.743 --> 35:01.409
Did you just quote "Bring It On"?

35:01.444 --> 35:02.643
Do you want the spirit stick or not?

35:02.679 --> 35:04.278
- Mm-hmm.
- Yes, I do.

35:04.314 --> 35:05.646
Okay, I just want to say

35:05.682 --> 35:07.582
I am really proud of you,

35:07.617 --> 35:10.485
and I'm so glad that we got to be there

35:10.520 --> 35:12.453
to witness your first big win.

35:12.489 --> 35:14.522
- I love you guys.
- I love you, too.

35:14.557 --> 35:16.424
[cell phone beeps]

35:19.396 --> 35:22.363
It's Adena.

35:22.399 --> 35:25.600
She's home, wants to talk.

35:27.470 --> 35:29.303
Thank you, wish me luck.

35:29.339 --> 35:31.372
- Good luck.
- Good luck.

35:31.408 --> 35:33.474
- You got this.
- Thank you.

35:33.510 --> 35:35.676
- Love you heaps.
- Heaps.

35:42.723 --> 35:44.474
_

35:54.664 --> 35:57.632
<i>[reflective music]</i>

35:57.667 --> 36:04.605
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:11.882 --> 36:14.595
_

36:28.665 --> 36:31.632
[door clicks]

36:36.773 --> 36:40.341
Wasn't sure if you'd come back.

36:40.376 --> 36:42.743
Well, I did.

36:42.779 --> 36:45.480
I'm ready to talk.

36:47.684 --> 36:50.384
Okay.

36:53.790 --> 36:58.326
I appreciate that you
were honest with me.

36:58.361 --> 37:01.295
I remember the first time...

37:01.331 --> 37:03.464
that I kissed a woman.

37:03.500 --> 37:05.633
It was...

37:05.668 --> 37:08.336
like fireworks everywhere.

37:10.773 --> 37:13.641
For you, there's only been me.

37:20.583 --> 37:22.550
Um, are you...

37:22.585 --> 37:24.552
Are you breaking up with me?

37:27.457 --> 37:30.358
I don't want to lose you.

37:30.393 --> 37:33.494
I don't want to lose you either.

37:33.530 --> 37:37.598
But this, this curiosity
that you have, Kat, it...

37:37.634 --> 37:39.767
doesn't just go away.

37:41.638 --> 37:43.471
So...

37:43.506 --> 37:45.773
what do we do?

37:51.447 --> 37:53.581
[sighs] I don't know.

38:04.394 --> 38:05.795
<i>[Elley Duhé's "Can You Touch"]</i>

38:05.894 --> 38:08.696
<i>♪ Hit the trap door
right next to the floor ♪</i>

38:08.731 --> 38:11.732
<i>♪ Every time we get too low ♪</i>

38:11.768 --> 38:14.368
<i>♪ Man, civil war... ♪</i>

38:14.404 --> 38:16.604
[cell phone rings]

38:19.709 --> 38:21.375
- Hello?
- Hey, Jane.

38:21.411 --> 38:22.810
It's Andrew, Jacqueline's assistant.

38:22.845 --> 38:24.779
Hi, Andrew. What's up?

38:24.814 --> 38:27.448
Jacqueline wants to see
you as soon as possible,

38:27.483 --> 38:28.749
Did she say why?

38:28.785 --> 38:30.551
Yeah, she told me all about it.

38:30.586 --> 38:31.886
I have no idea.

38:31.985 --> 38:34.522
- Uh...
- <i>[cell phone dial tone]</i>

38:34.557 --> 38:38.626
<i>♪ Hit the fuse,
and we'll do what we gotta do ♪</i>

38:38.661 --> 38:40.494
<i>♪ I don't break, I just groove ♪</i>

38:40.530 --> 38:41.862
<i>♪ I don't lose, hit the fuse ♪</i>

38:41.898 --> 38:45.866
<i>♪ And I'll do what I gotta do ♪</i>

38:45.902 --> 38:48.569
- Hey, look at that.
- Look at what?

38:48.604 --> 38:51.839
- You're early.
- Well, get used to it.

38:51.874 --> 38:55.409
<i>♪ Can you touch... ♪</i>

38:55.445 --> 38:56.644
Hey, Jane.

38:56.679 --> 38:58.646
She's waiting for you.

38:58.681 --> 39:00.748
- It's good to see you.
- Good to see you too.

39:00.783 --> 39:03.684
- Did you get taller?
- Did you get shorter?

39:10.760 --> 39:12.693
Jane, come in.

39:12.729 --> 39:14.695
Sit.

39:19.569 --> 39:21.569
So I read your article.

39:21.604 --> 39:23.471
And, uh...

39:23.506 --> 39:25.573
You could have left Elena out of it

39:25.608 --> 39:27.608
but you didn't.

39:27.643 --> 39:30.811
I didn't mean to cause you
any pain, but...

39:30.847 --> 39:34.381
you always taught me
that the story comes first.

39:34.417 --> 39:36.751
I know it's not my fault,
what happened to Elena.

39:36.786 --> 39:39.620
But I never considered...

39:39.655 --> 39:42.590
that there would be others after me.

39:42.625 --> 39:44.759
I managed to convince myself that...

39:44.794 --> 39:47.495
it would never happen again.

39:47.530 --> 39:52.500
Your article pushed me
to face the fact that it did.

39:52.535 --> 39:54.702
I've reached out to Elena
and we're gonna start

39:54.737 --> 39:56.837
working together to make sure
that there are safe spaces

39:56.873 --> 39:59.840
for women who want, or need,
to tell their stories.

39:59.876 --> 40:02.576
That's so great.

40:02.612 --> 40:05.880
When you came here
asking for your job back...

40:05.915 --> 40:07.681
you were in a place of fear.

40:07.717 --> 40:12.419
And when I said that you weren't ready
to return to Scarlet I meant that.

40:12.455 --> 40:16.724
But this article and the Jane

40:16.759 --> 40:19.527
that I've seen in the past few days

40:19.562 --> 40:21.562
is not fearful at all.

40:25.568 --> 40:27.535
Thank you.

40:30.807 --> 40:33.808
I want you back at Scarlet, Jane.

40:34.811 --> 40:37.912
If you're interested.

40:37.947 --> 40:39.580
We've missed you.

40:40.644 --> 40:42.788
I missed you.

40:45.371 --> 40:46.862
What's going on with you and Adena?

40:47.406 --> 40:48.698
I don't know.

40:48.699 --> 40:50.605
We're on uncharted territory.

40:51.267 --> 40:52.376
You're gonna be okay.

40:53.425 --> 40:54.995
Yeah, hope so.

40:58.428 --> 40:59.487
Jane?

40:59.488 --> 41:00.488
What are you doing here?

41:00.847 --> 41:03.689
Huh, hello? Excuse me, Jane?

41:03.724 --> 41:06.640
- Hello? What are you doing here?
- What are you doing here?

41:06.676 --> 41:07.894
I work here.

41:07.944 --> 41:09.743
- Ugh, Jane, we're fragile.
- Don't.

41:09.779 --> 41:12.713
- I work here.
- You're back?

41:12.748 --> 41:14.849
[cheering]

41:14.884 --> 41:16.650
Oh, my God!

41:16.686 --> 41:19.620
- When did that happen?
- Five minutes ago!

41:31.601 --> 41:34.568
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

41:34.604 --> 41:41.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

